cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on a wireless powered mobile edge computing system with device-to-device communication links, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization of communication and computation resources, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a joint optimization scheme for energy beamforming, resource allocation, and user-helper pairing, which can be considered as a control problem. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with distributed multi-antenna energy transmitters and distributed computation offloading, which are relevant to distributed computing. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the computation rate, which can be related to multimedia processing.
